India’s Subbarao Said to Be Offered Two-Year Extension as RBI’s Governor

-- B y   K a r t i k   G o y a l
-- 
2011-08-09T06:30:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/governor-subbarao-said-to-be-offered-two-year-extension-at-central-bank.html
Duvvuri Subbarao, scheduled to retire
as the governor of the  Reserve Bank  of  India  on Sept. 4, has
been offered a two-year extension, according to a government
official who didn’t wish to be identified because he isn’t
authorized to speak to the media on the subject.  Alpana Killawala, the Reserve Bank’s spokeswoman, couldn’t
immediately comment on the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kartik Goyal in New Delhi at 
 kgoyal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sam Nagarajan at 
 samnagarajan@bloomberg.net  